name: Apartment in the center of Lisbon
Cosy 3 Bedrooms Apartment @ Campolide
description:
HOUSE RENTALS -- A perfect place to rest, just like home.

Three bedroom apartment in the 1st floor, located in a quiet and safe residential area (Campolide), with several neighborhood shops and transports to the Lisbon downtown.
neighborhood_overview:
HOUSE RENTALS @ CAMPOLIDE

Campolide was once a good farmland. Nowadays these hills "hide" a calm and safe neighborhood, with houses mainly from the 70s. Almost the whole neighborhood is composed by buildings, but there is a very interesting zone - Calçada dos Mestres -, overlooking the Aqueduto das Águas Livres, where we find townhouses with backyards. Here live young people, old people and families. There is the movement of those who leave in the morning and come back at night, but also of those who live here during the day.

The Aqueduto das Águas Livres is an emblematic and grandiose work of Lisbon from the 18th century, its a complex system of abstraction and distribution of water to the city. A must do visit for those who do not know.

Near traditional stores with food products, as well as supermarkets (Pingo Doce and MyAuchan), there are also traditional Portuguese and Japanese restaurants. Campolide is connected to Lisbon's downtowns by public tr

name: 3 Bedrooms, 3 bathrooms and terrace - Chiado
host_about:
I started restoring our family property in Vila Real in the year 2000 and in 2010 had already 7 cottages ready for my guests. I love to restore old buildings and give them life. That's why it's so nice to have guests and children playing and to look at the cottages and see smoke coming out from the chimneys or the table set outside for a nice meal. I became so addicted to this transformation - from old ruins to nice and comfortable apartments-  that in 2008 i bought a flat in Lisbon to restore and rent to visitors. I wish I could go on and on buying, restoring and renting.
Apart from this “hobby” that became my job, I also love to travel and get new ideas for my guests.
My father is a wine producer in the Douro Valley and I always try to find time to share a  bottle and knowledge about Portuguese wines with my guests. So, this is it, my 2 passions in life: the farm and the winery and of course my 2 girls, the odest is 16 and a one year old baby.

name: Sunny flat with private patio
description: This beautiful sunny groundfloor studio/1 bed flat (55 sq. meters) with air con has been totally refurbished in 2015. The studio is located in Alfama - at the heart of Lisbon's old city. You have your own patio to soak up the sun! House has wifi.
neighborhood_overview: Alfama is one of the oldest and most typical neighbourhoods of Lisbon.
host_about:
I'm originally from Lisbon and love the light the city has to offer and its' hidden gems.

I have lived in London since 2003. I originally came to study and have worked as an arts producer/ fundraiser for the last 8 years.

I have run a number of international projects with young people that have taken me to places like China, Indonesia and Poland.

I love finding new places to eat and exploring the less known areas of the city.

My mum (Isabel) will be your local contact when you get to Lisbon. She is a history teacher with heaps of knowledge on the city. She lives just around the corner from the flat and will be happy to help with anything.

I am always happy to help and answer any of your queries and give you recommendations of things to do.

name: True Portuguese Experience @ Alfama
description:
Let us share with you what our culture is all about in one of the most historical spots of Lisbon.

Our apartment is located on the third floor of one of the most typical streets in the heart of Alfama.

name: Apartment with river views in the heart of Alfama
description:
Amazing 1-bed apartment with stunning river views in the heart of Alfama.

Located minutes away from Santa Apolonia train/metro station, in one of the most iconic streets of Lisbon.

You will be within easy reach of all major sightseeing attractions and typical restaurants and bars are just around the corner.

The apartment has been redecorated in Aug 2016 including a brand new kitchen.

We live around the corner and are happy to offer recommendations and help you with any queries/ problems.
host_about:
I'm originally from Lisbon and love the light the city has to offer and its' hidden gems.

I have lived in London since 2003. I originally came to study and have worked as an arts producer/ fundraiser for the last 8 years.

I have run a number of international projects with young people that have taken me to places like China, Indonesia and Poland.

I love finding new places to eat and exploring the less known areas of the city.

My mum (Isabel) will be your local contact when you get to Lisbon. She is a history teacher with heaps of knowledge on the city. She lives just around the corner from the flat and will be happy to help with anything.

I am always happy to help and answer any of your queries and give you recommendations of things to do.

host_about:
As a native Lisboner, I love everything around Portugal heritage, hospitality and kindness. Living in the city center gives me possibility to do really cool programmes like dancing Forro at Avenida da Liberdade, shop at Baixa Chiado ou walk near the river.
Would love to share with you my passion for this city, which regardless of living in other countries, is still my favourite!

neighborhood_overview:
HOUSE RENTALS @ CAMPOLIDE

Campolide was once a good farmland. Nowadays these hills "hide" a calm and safe neighborhood, with houses mainly from the 70s. Almost the whole neighborhood is composed by buildings, but there is a very interesting zone - Calçada dos Mestres -, overlooking the Aqueduto das Águas Livres, where we find townhouses with backyards. Here live young people, old people and families. There is the movement of those who leave in the morning and come back at night, but also of those who live here during the day.

The Aqueduto das Águas Livres is an emblematic and grandiose work of Lisbon from the 18th century, its a complex system of abstraction and distribution of water to the city. A must do visit for those who do not know.

description:
Gather in the peaceful courtyard like the locals do, or curl up with some tea and quiet time under the beams in the cozy living space. This artisan-restored cottage enchants with an impeccable modern aesthetic that respects its original architecture.

Patio São Vicente is tucked away in the corner of the Telheiro do Sao Vicente square in a private Patio. The cottages of “Patio São Vicente” have been completely restored respecting the original architecture yet designed with a modern aesthetic by Paratelier architects. Using Portuguese artisans and designers, the interiors are cosy, comfortable and carefully crafted with custom carpentry.

The buildings are of historic importance. The 13th century original wall of Lisbon the “Muralha Fernandina” is integrated into the back wall of each of the living rooms. The corner turret is visible from the courtyard and can be accessed by the garden of one the apartments.

name: Experience Central Lisbon from a Charming Apartment
description:
Tile House 95 is in a gorgeous historic building from the beginning of the 20th century. Newly renovated, the decor uses natural and ecological materials to create basket-woven fixtures that create a welcoming and calming ambiance. House Rules: No pets allowed, smoking is forbidden, parties not permitted, Long term Rentals (more than 14 nights) power consumption, water and Wi-Fi+TV are not included on the rental and have to be paid separately. A deposit of €200 will be asked upon check in to ensure the payment of the consumption after the check out.

The apartment has two bedrooms, one - the master suite – with a king-size bed and private bathroom, a living room, a second bathroom, a balcony and a fully equipped kitchen where you can cook with the ingredients bought at the nearby traditional market.

name: Cosy Studio in Center
description: Enjoy a cozy studio on the ground floor of an apartment in Lisbon, conveniently located near Arroios and Martim Moniz. This apartment places you within easy walking distance of the subway and the heart of Lisbon's city center, making it the perfect base for exploring the city's charm and attractions.
neighborhood_overview:
Discover Arroios, a vibrant neighborhood in the heart of Lisbon that blends Portuguese tradition with a multicultural atmosphere. Centrally located, Arroios is perfect for exploring on foot, with easy access to charming cafés, traditional restaurants, and innovative boutiques.

Enjoy the convenience of being just steps away from some of the city's top attractions. Visit the Senhora do Monte viewpoint for a stunning view of Lisbon, or explore the historic São Jorge Castle, both just a short metro or bus ride away. The area is also rich in culture, with several art galleries and cultural spaces reflecting the neighborhood's vibrant art scene.

Arroios is the ideal destination for those seeking an authentic experience and a convenient starting point to discover the best of Lisbon.

neighborhood_overview:
Are you ready to discover new things?
The history of the village of Cascais is linked to the history of Europe, many royal families and other Portuguese families. Here are the best ways to get to know it.


A stroll through some of the best museums in the village, a hotel that inspired the birth of James Bond and a massage in a place that was home for Italian kings.


Cascais. Always linked to some of the great landmarks of the Portugal's history, thanks to the proximity of Lisbon and the strategic point it occupies on the map, to the West. As such, you have to turn some leisure days into cultural lessons about Cascais.

neighborhood_overview:
HOUSE RENTALS @ CAMPOLIDE

Campolide was once a good farmland. Nowadays these hills "hide" a calm and safe neighborhood, with houses mainly from the 70s. Almost the whole neighborhood is composed by buildings, but there is a very interesting zone - Calçada dos Mestres -, overlooking the Aqueduto das Águas Livres, where we find townhouses with backyards. Here live young people, old people and families. There is the movement of those who leave in the morning and come back at night, but also of those who live here during the day.

The Aqueduto das Águas Livres is an emblematic and grandiose work of Lisbon from the 18th century, its a complex system of abstraction and distribution of water to the city. A must do visit for those who do not know.

name: 3 bedrooms 3 bathrooms, at the heart of Chiado
description:
Penthouse apartment on the third floor of an XVIII Cent. building with an ample staircase but no lift.

The top-floor apart has 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, a fully-equipped kitchen, a spacious living room with a view, and air-conditioning.

Walking distances are: tram 28 line (3 min.), Chiado Metro (5 min.), Cais do Sodré trains to Cascais and the Estoril line beaches (5 min.) and Rossio train station to Sintra (15 min.)

Chiado boasts some of our beautiful city's best restaurants and cafés.
host_about:
I started restoring our family property in Vila Real in the year 2000 and in 2010 had already 7 cottages ready for my guests. I love to restore old buildings and give them life. That's why it's so nice to have guests and children playing and to look at the cottages and see smoke coming out from the chimneys or the table set outside for a nice meal. I became so addicted to this transformation - from old ruins to nice and comfortable apartments-  that in 2008 i bought a flat in Lisbon to restore and rent to visitors. I wish I could go on and on buying, restoring and renting.
Apart from this “hobby” that became my job, I also love to travel and get new ideas for my guests.
My father is a wine producer in the Douro Valley and I always try to find time to share a  bottle and knowledge about Portuguese wines with my guests. So, this is it, my 2 passions in life: the farm and the winery and of course my 2 girls, the odest is 16 and a one year old baby.
